    • Field Detail

      • idleThreshold

        public final long idleThreshold
        The idle detection threshold, that is, the duration of user inactivity. The unit is Millisecond.
        When this threshold is reached, the event TcrSession.Event.CLIENT_IDLE will be triggered.

      • lowFpsThresholdCount

        public final int lowFpsThresholdCount
        The frame rate threshold. If the value is less than 0, detection will be disabled.
        When the frame rate is lower than fps and the duration exceeds duration second, the event TcrSession.Event.CLIENT_LOW_FPS will be triggered.

      • lowFpsThresholdDuration

        public final int lowFpsThresholdDuration
        The frame rate duration threshold. If the value is less than 0, detection will be disabled. The unit is Second.
        When the frame rate is lower than fps and the duration exceeds duration second, the event TcrSession.Event.CLIENT_LOW_FPS will be triggered.

      • preferredCodecList

        public final java.util.ArrayList<TcrSessionConfig.VideoCodecType> preferredCodecList
        The preferred codec list.

        Indicate preferred codecs, where the order of the elements in the list represents priority, such as index 0 being the highest priority preferred codec. If the set codecs cannot be selected for various reasons, other available codecs will be chosen.

      • enableCustomAudioCapture

        public final boolean enableCustomAudioCapture
        Indicates whether custom audio capture is enabled (true) or disabled (false). TcrSessionConfig.Builder.enableCustomAudioCapture(boolean, int, boolean) TcrSession.sendCustomAudioData(ByteBuffer, long)

      • inputSampleRate

        public final int inputSampleRate
        The sample rate (in Hz) of the input audio, e.g., 44100 or 48000. TcrSessionConfig.Builder.enableCustomAudioCapture(boolean, int, boolean) TcrSession.sendCustomAudioData(ByteBuffer, long)

        public final boolean useStereoInput

      • enableLowLegacyRendering

        public final boolean enableLowLegacyRendering
        Turn on low-latency rendering.
        Rendering delay will be reduced when turned on.
        When the network condition is good, the delay is significantly reduced after opening. When the network condition is poor, there may be a freeze phenomenon.
